The paper deals with online learning techniques and stochastic gradient descent solvers for non-decomposable loss functions, which are commonly used in sensitive domains such as biometrics and medicine. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Computer Vision (cs.CV), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-categories.
